-- Eurasian Minerals Sells Slovakia, Peru Geothermal Energy Assets
-- B y   S t e p h a n   N i e l s e n
-- 2013-08-07T12:55:14Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-08-07/eurasian-minerals-sells-slovakia-peru-geothermal-energy-assets.html
Eurasian Minerals Inc. (EMX) , a Canadian
mineral-exploration company, sold its geothermal projects in
Slovakia and  Peru  to Starlight Geothermal Ltd. in return for a 5
percent equity stake in the company.  Eurasian Minerals also received an undisclosed cash payment
and will get royalties from the projectsâ€™ future energy
production, the Vancouver-based company said today in a
statement.  Eurasian Minerals had five licenses in Slovakia totaling
320 square kilometers (123.6 square miles) and four in Peru
totaling 328 square kilometers, according to the statement.  To contact the reporter on this story:
